21:48.308 --> 21:49.639
...to talk to Officer....

21:50.059 --> 21:51.765
Stackhouse.

21:52.687 --> 21:54.393
You mean Jason.

21:54.856 --> 21:57.689
I didn't get a first name. Just Stackhouse.

21:57.901 --> 21:59.141
[CHUCKLES]

22:00.278 --> 22:03.270
[VACUUM WHIRRING AND UPBEAT MUSIC
PLAYING OVER EARPHONES]

22:03.490 --> 22:05.481
[PHONE RINGING]

22:09.954 --> 22:11.490
[WHIRRING STOPS]

22:13.875 --> 22:15.490
Yeah, Stackhouse.

22:15.668 --> 22:17.204
Hoyt's here, Jason.

22:17.921 --> 22:20.333
-What? Hoyt? He's where?
-At the BB&G.

22:20.507 --> 22:24.216
-He's acting like he doesn't even know you.
-Yeah, that's because he doesn't.

22:24.385 --> 22:27.047
Listen, Arlene, do not say
anything to him, all right?

22:27.222 --> 22:29.304
-I'm on my way.
-Okay.

22:36.105 --> 22:37.641
SO...

22:38.775 --> 22:41.312
-...should I use this on you?
-Uh....

22:41.486 --> 22:43.727
How much does it say to use?

22:44.697 --> 22:47.439
Um.... It doesn't.

22:48.910 --> 22:52.027
All it says is that its chief ingredient
is horny goat weed.

22:52.205 --> 22:55.322
It "Invigorates the sensory nerves
while restoring the adrenals...

22:55.500 --> 22:57.707
...and alleviating fatigue for...

22:57.877 --> 22:59.208
...a stress-reducing effect."

23:01.130 --> 23:03.621
You wanna try something else, then?

23:12.850 --> 23:16.092
WADE:
Okay, just keep cool. Be a man.

23:16.271 --> 23:19.058
If she '5 into this stuff,
you gotta do Whatever it takes...

23:19.232 --> 23:22.816
...to please your woman,
even if you ain 't into this at all.

23:23.027 --> 23:25.404
-Oh, thank God.
-What?

23:25.572 --> 23:27.312
You're not into this.

23:27.490 --> 23:29.822
-Are you?
-NO.

23:29.993 --> 23:31.073
Oh, my God. Thank you.

23:31.244 --> 23:34.111
NO, thank you. You have no idea
how happy you just made me.

23:34.289 --> 23:35.995
I thought you wanted to experiment.

23:36.165 --> 23:39.328
NO, and I thought that you wanted to
on account of you being...

23:39.502 --> 23:41.868
-...so much more experienced than me.
-Wait, what?

23:43.131 --> 23:45.417
-What?
-Listen, I'm--

23:45.592 --> 23:48.049
I'm not more experienced.

23:48.219 --> 23:49.425
I mean...

23:49.596 --> 23:50.836
...Our first time...

23:51.264 --> 23:52.549
...was my first time.

23:54.475 --> 23:56.056
Mine too.

23:56.561 --> 23:58.392
I really do love you, Wade Cleary.

23:58.563 --> 23:59.643
I love you too.

24:04.986 --> 24:06.146
[DOOR OPENS]

24:06.321 --> 24:08.312
[SLOW MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

24:14.370 --> 24:15.871
ARLENE:
That is Hoyt's girlfriend.

24:32.138 --> 24:33.924
-Mr. Fortenberry?
-Ahem.

24:34.098 --> 24:35.804
-Officer Stackhouse?
-YeS, sir.

24:35.975 --> 24:38.011
I'm Hoyt Fortenberry. This is my girlfriend.

24:38.186 --> 24:39.767
Brigette.

24:40.313 --> 24:43.976
It's nice to meet you too.

24:44.400 --> 24:47.392
Though I'm sorry about the circumstances.

24:49.489 --> 24:51.104
Well, uh...

24:51.407 --> 24:53.693
...to be honest, ahem, you know...

24:53.868 --> 24:56.200
...I try not to think about it.

24:56.537 --> 24:57.913
Itjust all seems SO unreal.

24:58.915 --> 25:01.031
-Hmm.
-It'll probably feel more real...

25:01.209 --> 25:03.575
...Once you go and see her. Hmm?

25:03.795 --> 25:05.660
HOYT:
Yeah, I don't know if...

25:05.838 --> 25:07.669
...I'm ready for all that yet, but....

25:08.466 --> 25:10.127
You wanna join us for breakfast?

25:11.219 --> 25:12.959
-Hmm?
-You wanna join us for breakfast?

25:13.137 --> 25:15.594
Oh, you guys finish up. I'll just...

25:15.765 --> 25:18.381
-...be waiting over at the bar.
-NO, don't be ridiculous.

25:18.851 --> 25:20.887
NO, please. We insist.

25:31.948 --> 25:34.439
[UTENSILS CLATTER
THEN HOYT CHUCKLES]

25:34.617 --> 25:35.732
It's okay.

25:35.910 --> 25:37.446
Sorry about that.

25:38.371 --> 25:40.362
[ROCK MUSIC BLARING OVER CAR STEREO]

25:46.754 --> 25:47.789
[MUSIC STOPS]

26:00.560 --> 26:03.097
Dr. Ludwig, thank you for coming
on such short notice.

26:03.271 --> 26:05.353
-Where's the patient?
-At his house.

26:05.648 --> 26:07.263
I would've had you meet me there...

26:07.442 --> 26:09.933
...with him being a vampire,
I thought this was safer.

26:10.111 --> 26:13.729
Next time, save yourself some money and
have me meet you where the patient is.

26:13.906 --> 26:18.115
I fear nothing and no one,
and I have no natural enemies.

26:18.286 --> 26:19.526
Well, where is he?

26:21.164 --> 26:22.244
Across the cemetery.

26:22.790 --> 26:26.658
Ooh. How very spooky. A cemetery. Shall we?

26:34.635 --> 26:36.626
[CHATTERING]

26:44.520 --> 26:46.226
There she is.

26:46.397 --> 26:49.560
-Where?
WILLIAM: Right over there with the Shelbys.

26:54.030 --> 26:55.566
William.

26:55.740 --> 26:56.855
-Stewart.
-Claire.

26:57.533 --> 26:59.194
Margaret.

27:09.420 --> 27:11.627
And you must be Caroline.

27:18.846 --> 27:20.347
CAROLINE:
I have to admit...

27:20.515 --> 27:22.972
...you're not what I was expecting.

27:23.518 --> 27:25.634
What were you expecting?

27:25.978 --> 27:27.184
Well, your daddy.

27:27.355 --> 27:29.220
Only younger...

27:29.982 --> 27:32.064
-...and just aS--
-Rotund?

27:32.276 --> 27:34.141
[BOTH LAUGH]

27:34.320 --> 27:36.402
NO, I take after my mother.

27:37.698 --> 27:41.282
The truth be told, Caroline, you're not
quite what I was expecting either.

27:42.703 --> 27:44.204
Oh?

27:44.914 --> 27:46.870
And what were you expecting?

27:48.459 --> 27:51.622
My father described you as "comely."

27:52.213 --> 27:54.454
-Well, comely is a good thing.
-I know it is...

27:54.632 --> 27:57.294
...but that word is just so anachronistic...

27:57.468 --> 28:00.050
-...that I suppose I thought you'd be--
-Old and dowdy?

28:01.055 --> 28:02.386
Formerly pretty, yes.

28:02.598 --> 28:03.713
[LAUGHS]

28:06.602 --> 28:09.890
You feel their eyes on us
as aggressively as I do?

28:10.064 --> 28:12.976
Now that you mention it,
I can feel all eight of their eyes...

28:13.150 --> 28:15.687
...searing a hole into the back of my head.

28:15.903 --> 28:16.983
[BILL CHUCKLES]

28:19.574 --> 28:20.905
[CHUCKLES]

28:22.368 --> 28:24.825
Would you care to take a walk with me?

28:24.996 --> 28:26.577
I would.

28:29.625 --> 28:30.876
LU DWIG:
Mr. Compton.

28:31.043 --> 28:32.874
Mr. Compton.

28:33.045 --> 28:35.627
-Mr. Compton.
-Careful, he doesn't like to be woken.

28:35.798 --> 28:39.586
Like I said, I fear nothing and no one.
Mr. Compton!

28:39.760 --> 28:41.216
[HISSES]

28:42.680 --> 28:44.261
Remember me?

28:44.932 --> 28:47.218
-Doctor?
-Ludwig.

28:47.393 --> 28:50.305
Put your fangs away, son,
and meet me in the parlor.

28:54.775 --> 28:59.314
Mm-mm. Nasty, nasty, nasty.

29:00.364 --> 29:02.355
Congratulations, Mr. Compton.

29:02.533 --> 29:06.617
They said it could not be done,
but you have thoroughly grossed me out.

29:06.787 --> 29:07.867
Can you help him?

29:08.039 --> 29:11.202
How many days ago
do you believe you were infected?

29:11.584 --> 29:14.826
Don't look to her. I'm the one
that asked you the question.

29:15.004 --> 29:18.371
I gotta say, Dr. Ludwig, I'm a little curious
about your bedside manner.

29:18.549 --> 29:20.005
LU DWIG:
Newsflash.

29:24.013 --> 29:26.846
...and something altogether different
to their vampire lovers.

29:27.016 --> 29:28.472
We are no longer lovers.

29:28.643 --> 29:32.511
-Are you sure she knows that?
-He contracted the virus from me.

29:32.688 --> 29:34.599
I was exposed through a cut in my arm.

29:34.774 --> 29:37.265
He drank my blood and got sick
pretty much right away.

29:37.777 --> 29:40.314
I'm sorry, but that's not
how this virus works.

29:40.488 --> 29:43.150
Would it make any difference
if Sookie was a halfling?

29:43.324 --> 29:44.404
Half what?

29:44.575 --> 29:46.440
-Half fae?
SOOKIE: Mm-hm.

29:46.744 --> 29:50.703
A few weeks ago, I was called to the home
of a sick vampire in Monroe.

29:50.873 --> 29:53.785
He had a not dissimilarly
accelerated rate of infection.

29:53.960 --> 29:56.622
Went from stage one
to stage three in 10 days.

29:56.963 --> 29:59.670
I was perplexed until he revealed to me...

29:59.840 --> 30:02.377
...that his boyfriend
was a Hep-V positive fairy.

30:02.551 --> 30:05.213
He was no halfling, mind you.
He was the real deal.

30:05.388 --> 30:09.256
And even SO, he didn't look anywhere
near as bad as Mr. Compton does.

30:10.184 --> 30:12.425
DO you happen to know
the name of your line?

30:12.687 --> 30:15.724
-My line?
-Come on, missy. Your fairy line.

30:15.898 --> 30:18.310
-Your lineage.
-I don't know.

30:18.484 --> 30:21.601
I don't know the name.
I guess I could ask Niall.

30:22.321 --> 30:23.731
Niall Brigant?

30:25.074 --> 30:26.154
Yeah, do you know him?

30:26.325 --> 30:27.940
Are you related to Niall Brigant?

30:28.119 --> 30:31.452
Yeah, he's my great-great-great—
times-a-thousand-grandfather. Why?

30:33.165 --> 30:34.701
I'm so fucking out of here.

30:34.875 --> 30:37.161
-Dr. Ludwig?
-|'|| Show myself out.

30:49.140 --> 30:52.257
Goddamn it, Stackhouse.
Get your fucking eyes Off her.

30:52.852 --> 30:54.934
I should've been here.

30:56.856 --> 30:59.222
Maybe I could've saved her.

30:59.734 --> 31:01.520
At least just--

31:02.069 --> 31:05.106
Just been here for her
when it happened or something.

31:05.281 --> 31:06.646
BRIGETTE:
Hey.

31:07.992 --> 31:10.358
You can't blame yourself.

31:10.995 --> 31:14.908
And I'm sure if she were here right now,
your mama would tell you the same thing.

31:15.082 --> 31:18.574
NO, she wouldn't. If She were here
right now, she'd lay it on thick.

31:19.170 --> 31:21.877
God, what I wouldn't give
for one more guilt trip.

31:23.007 --> 31:24.042
[HOYT CRYING]

31:33.142 --> 31:34.848
-[MOUTHING] Hey.
-Huh?

31:35.186 --> 31:36.676
Can you come in here, please?

31:39.440 --> 31:40.429
[SOFTLY]
Shit.

31:45.154 --> 31:46.860
[WHISPERS]
Hi.

31:47.156 --> 31:48.236
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Did you know Maxine?

31:49.658 --> 31:52.650
Um-- Yeah, yeah, a little.

31:52.828 --> 31:54.204
Good.

31:54.371 --> 31:57.113
I think he needs to talk to somebody
who knew her.

31:57.291 --> 31:59.998
DO you think you could just go
and talk to him, maybe?

32:02.296 --> 32:03.832
Yeah.

32:04.006 --> 32:05.587
Thank you.

32:09.804 --> 32:11.169
[SNIFFLING]

32:12.765 --> 32:14.130
Uh....

32:14.517 --> 32:16.257
I know it's hard, Mr. Fortenberry.

32:16.435 --> 32:17.971
How'd it happen?

32:18.479 --> 32:21.516
-Huh?
-How'd she die?

32:22.233 --> 32:26.772
Um.... Well, you remember Vince McNeil?

32:27.404 --> 32:29.656
-He's the orthodontist?
-Yeah.

32:29.824 --> 32:31.405
Yeah, that's him.

32:32.785 --> 32:34.321
Um....

32:35.538 --> 32:39.247
Well, when the Shit hit the fan
at the BB&G last week...

32:39.583 --> 32:42.325
...Mr. McNeil...

32:42.503 --> 32:44.960
...he got a bunch of the townsfolk
all riled up...

32:45.673 --> 32:48.460
...and together they took the law...

32:48.634 --> 32:50.795
...into their own hands.

32:51.804 --> 32:53.214
Was my mama one of them?

32:57.768 --> 32:59.144
NO, that--

32:59.562 --> 33:00.972
NO.

33:01.814 --> 33:03.850
NO, she was not.

33:05.901 --> 33:08.313
She was one of the good folks.

33:10.906 --> 33:13.192
Did you get the son of a bitch
that did it to her?

33:13.409 --> 33:15.821
Mm-hm. Yeah.

33:18.330 --> 33:20.161
Yeah, I sure did.

33:21.584 --> 33:23.370
Thank you, man.

33:58.829 --> 34:00.660
Grandpa Niall?

34:04.919 --> 34:08.036
You know I've been in
a lot of situations lately.

34:08.214 --> 34:12.332
I had plenty of good reasons
to call on a fairy godfather...

34:12.927 --> 34:15.794
...but I didn't.

34:18.891 --> 34:20.097
Until now...

34:20.726 --> 34:24.765
...because I like to think of myself as strong.

34:27.024 --> 34:29.731
But I ain't this strong.

34:30.694 --> 34:33.310
If you're listening, Grandpa Niall...

34:33.489 --> 34:35.855
...I need you to materialize...

34:36.242 --> 34:37.778
...right here...

34:37.952 --> 34:39.908
...right now.

34:40.120 --> 34:42.111
[WIND WHISTLING]

34:49.964 --> 34:53.422
Oh. You know what? Fuck this.

35:01.183 --> 35:03.094
[DOOR HANDLE RATTLING]

35:07.982 --> 35:09.097
[OBJECTS CLATTERING]

35:09.358 --> 35:11.098
Jesus Christ.

35:11.277 --> 35:13.063
-Nia||.
-Hi.

35:13.237 --> 35:15.478
How do you make that wonderful spaghetti?

35:15.656 --> 35:18.898
This is so good.

35:20.869 --> 35:23.326
-Can we go now?
-NO.

35:23.497 --> 35:24.612
Food first.

35:24.790 --> 35:28.203
-One mustn't forget to nourish oneself.
-Please.

35:28.377 --> 35:31.619
-I don't know how much time he has left.
-I understand...

35:31.797 --> 35:35.210
...but if this munchkin doctor
doesn't know how to heal him...

35:35.384 --> 35:36.544
...what can I do?

35:38.137 --> 35:39.547
You were watching?

35:39.847 --> 35:41.883
I'm always watching you.

35:42.391 --> 35:44.928
DO you know why she was
so afraid of you, then?

35:45.102 --> 35:46.308
We are royalty.

35:47.021 --> 35:50.104
Dwarves have an innate fear of us.

35:50.482 --> 35:54.646
Maybe because we killed
so many of them in the past.

35:57.323 --> 36:01.612
I just realized
that if you're always watching...

36:02.578 --> 36:04.068
...did you know...

36:04.246 --> 36:07.864
...I was infecting Bill
when he was feeding off of me?

36:08.542 --> 36:10.043
I did.

36:11.170 --> 36:12.535
Why would you let me do that?

36:12.963 --> 36:16.046
-I don't like him.
-You don't have to like him.

36:16.216 --> 36:18.377
You're doing something for me.

36:18.552 --> 36:20.508
What I meant was...

36:20.679 --> 36:23.591
...I don't like him for you.

36:25.184 --> 36:26.515
[SNIFFLES]

36:26.894 --> 36:28.509
Grandpa Niall...

36:28.687 --> 36:30.678
...you say we're royalty...

36:30.856 --> 36:34.269
...but other than the vampire-killing
light ball...

36:34.443 --> 36:37.606
...that I can only use once, by the way...

36:37.780 --> 36:41.318
...I can't think of a single fucking
advantage in being what we are.

36:42.201 --> 36:45.159
If you say that we're so fucking special...

36:45.996 --> 36:48.203
...I am asking you...

36:50.084 --> 36:51.995
...I'm begging you...

36:53.587 --> 36:54.827
...prove it.

36:55.005 --> 36:57.291
Use some of your magic for me.

36:59.718 --> 37:01.709
Fine, Sookie.

37:02.221 --> 37:04.007
I'll try.

37:13.607 --> 37:15.143
[SARAH BREATHING HEAVILY]

37:26.870 --> 37:29.862
[WOMAN SINGING
AND PEOPLE CHATTERING]

37:31.417 --> 37:33.408
[WOMAN AND CROWD SINGING]

37:38.674 --> 37:40.665
[CROWD CLAPPING AND SINGING]

37:49.226 --> 37:50.807
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

37:53.689 --> 37:56.146
[PEOPLE CHEERING]

37:56.316 --> 37:58.147
[MEN GRUNTING]

37:58.318 --> 37:59.774
MAN 1 :
Watch him.

38:00.446 --> 38:02.186
MAN 2:
That's how you catch it.

38:02.698 --> 38:04.689
[WHOOSHING]

38:06.285 --> 38:11.245
There it is. H00. H00.
Hoo-hoo-hoo.

38:11.415 --> 38:12.871
Jason?

38:14.209 --> 38:16.791
Jason? Over here.

38:17.045 --> 38:21.914
-Oh. Hey, Noomi.
-Oh, God, I'm so glad you're here.

38:22.092 --> 38:23.502
I feel so alone.

38:24.052 --> 38:27.044
Oh. Well, we all die alone.

38:27.473 --> 38:28.588
What?

38:28.765 --> 38:30.050
You're gonna die tonight.

38:30.225 --> 38:33.558
See, Eric's coming for you,
and there ain't no escaping it.

38:34.730 --> 38:36.721
But I don't wanna die.

38:36.940 --> 38:39.477
Ha-ha-ha. Well, that's just too fucking bad.

38:39.651 --> 38:42.939
See, death comes for all of us...

38:43.113 --> 38:44.398
...and your number's up.

38:45.991 --> 38:47.492
NO.

38:48.327 --> 38:49.362
You're not real.

38:50.329 --> 38:52.445
Maybe not, but death is.

38:53.665 --> 38:55.997
-Fuck off.
-Yeah, I'll be sure to do that, then.

38:56.543 --> 38:58.955
I'll see you in hell when I get there.

38:59.129 --> 39:01.245
There is no hell.

39:02.341 --> 39:03.330
[CHUCKLES]

39:03.509 --> 39:05.670
You just try to convince yourself of that.

39:05.844 --> 39:07.550
You don't even know--

39:13.810 --> 39:15.220
Hold it together, Noomi.

39:15.395 --> 39:18.603
You are one with the universe.
Keep it together.

39:26.156 --> 39:27.191
MAN [I N JAPANESE]:

39:27.366 --> 39:29.448
We've got her.

39:38.377 --> 39:40.368
You can find another vampire.

39:47.761 --> 39:50.298
You know how on the news you see these....

39:50.597 --> 39:52.713
These places get...

39:52.891 --> 39:56.383
...wiped out by tornados...

39:56.728 --> 39:59.765
...but the people who live there are always...

39:59.940 --> 40:02.602
...vowing to rebuild
on the exact same Spot...

40:02.776 --> 40:05.734
...where tragedy took away
everything they had?

40:06.238 --> 40:07.603
I do.

40:07.781 --> 40:09.737
Am I as crazy as they are?

40:11.577 --> 40:14.944
I mean, is Nicole right?
Is this whole town crazy?

40:15.747 --> 40:20.081
Because I love her and I wanna be a father
to my baby girl...

40:21.336 --> 40:23.452
...but this ultimatum's got me.

40:27.217 --> 40:29.754
Why can't I wrap my head around
leaving this place?

40:29.928 --> 40:35.298
I mean, at what point does the guy
whose house keeps getting hit by a tornado...

40:35.475 --> 40:40.014
...call it a day, take his family,
move someplace else?

40:41.940 --> 40:44.682
I can't answer that for you, Sam.

40:46.278 --> 40:48.064
Let me ask you a question.

40:50.157 --> 40:52.113
Better pour me another one first.

41:02.878 --> 41:04.960
I know you, Sam.

41:05.672 --> 41:08.709
I know you better than I think you think I do.

41:09.092 --> 41:13.677
And so I know that you've spent your whole life
running away from things.

41:14.556 --> 41:18.424
Bon Temps is the only place
you actually stopped and stuck it out.

41:20.312 --> 41:22.769
I ain't heard a question yet.

41:25.233 --> 41:27.360
Ifyouleﬁ”.

41:27.986 --> 41:31.524
...do you think it would feel more
like you were running from something...

41:31.698 --> 41:34.314
...Or to something?

41:35.494 --> 41:36.700
Let me put it another way.

41:36.870 --> 41:38.986
If you stayed...

41:39.873 --> 41:43.491
...could you be happy here without them?

41:45.962 --> 41:49.329
When you can answer the question,
you'll know what to do.

41:53.261 --> 41:55.673
Are you happy here, Arlene?

41:56.848 --> 42:00.011
I mean, with everything
that's going on and--

42:00.185 --> 42:02.141
I take it.

42:04.106 --> 42:07.564
See, my hope is the more I fake it,
the more I'll believe it...

42:07.734 --> 42:09.599
...until the happiness becomes real.

42:11.113 --> 42:13.775
But, no, Sam, I ain't happy.

42:14.908 --> 42:18.071
But there ain't a chance in hell
I'm gonna stop trying to be.

42:20.414 --> 42:23.451
